# Security — landing (public, unauthenticated)

The landing is **fully public**. Only minimal, validated writes to Firestore are allowed. Rules live in **`four_drinking_admin/firestore.rules`** — coordinate changes there.

## Waitlist & Firestore writes

- Only write to collections explicitly allowed by rules (currently `waitlist` via `validWaitlistCreate()`).
- Payload must match rules: `email`, `createdAt` (server timestamp), `source: 'landing'`, optional `name` (max length per rules).
- Persist legal consent fields (`privacyAccepted`, versions, timestamps) consistently with `WaitlistService` — do not add fields rules reject.
- **Never** write from landing to `users`, admin collections, or authenticated-only paths.
- Do not embed Firebase Admin SDK or secrets in this repo — client SDK only.

## Input validation

- Validate email client-side (`isValidWaitlistEmail`) **and** rely on rules server-side — never trust browser input.
- Require explicit privacy acceptance before submit (`WaitlistForm` pattern).
- Generic error messages to users; no Firestore/security error details in UI.

## Legal & RGPD

- Store `privacyPolicyVersion`, `termsVersion`, `cookiePolicyVersion` from `LandingConfig` on waitlist docs.
- Marketing consent: optional, with timestamp when true.
- Link to legal pages on-site (`/privacidad`, etc.) — do not hotlink arbitrary URLs.

## Dependencies & hosting

- Static Flutter Web + Firestore client only — no Cloud Functions in this repo.
- Verify new packages are Web-safe; avoid `dart:io`.
- `firebase.json`: hosting only — do not add broad Firestore/Functions deploy config here.

## Definition of done (security)

- [ ] New Firestore writes have matching rules + tests in `four_drinking_admin`
- [ ] No auth secrets or admin capabilities in landing code
- [ ] Consent and version fields aligned with legal config
- [ ] User-facing errors do not leak permission/index details
